column1: Yeah, looks like the coast is clear...

That's surprising—I expected guards to be
posted here more so than anywhere else.
I can't exactly tell from over here...
This could actually be good for us.

There's only the one guy. If we capture him,
we might be able to question him.
Heh, don't worry. Leave it to the professional.

If we're all on the same page, then I'd better
get a move on.
You're doin' it by yourself, Gramps!?
I've been through enough training. I'll be fine.

You guys just stay here and keep an eye out
for any of his buddies.
Holy crap, Gramps just got way cooler!

Scoundrel! You dare defile our Lord's hallowed
ground!?
Oh wow... Watch your step there. You all right?
Not again!? You totally threw him on his ass!
He truly is a member of Public Security.
Hey, take a look at that.
The sign we saw this morning...
Look again—the 18th was changed to the 19th.

Apparently the facility's staff is on permanent
vacation, one day at a time.

Most likely? To string along anyone who came
to the island for the lab.

When someone thinks the staff's out for the day,
they probably stick around the island.

Come nighttime, the locals descend on whoever
got too curious... To protect whatever's in there.

If his heart's been changed, he should have
a smartphone with EMMA installed.

Yep, there's EMMA all right. Aaaand...
he only has one Friend?

There's a chance this Ubukata is the Monarch of
Okinawa.
Hmm, that one's a lot tougher...
Oh, hang on! There's an email here!

"Cordial invitation to serve as a tester of the
EMMA system"...
Whoa, this even has a keyword in it!

I don't recognize the address... Maybe it's from
the lab?

The lab asked all of these guys to be EMMA
testers...?

What now? Thanks to the email, we know the
keyword's "Operation Oraculi."

If the people who call this place "hallowed"
had their hearts changed, then it's going to
be Jail-related, without a doubt.
But, like, we can't find a Jail here. Right, Sophia?

I'm not sure... At the very least, I do not smell
one.
One way to know for sure.
He's right. If we can't get in, that'll settle it.

But—if there IS a Jail here, testing the keyword
will send us right in.

We have no choice but to try. Our pursuers
have decided our path.

Yeah, even the Metaverse feels safer to me than
this place does now.

EMMA, add Shuzo Ubukata to my Friend
Registry. Keyword: "Operation Oraculi"!
The scent is already all around us!
